	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64109475"><p>Geometry suggests that it's a net negative.  Each circle of latitude (of a give width) as you get closer to the poles contains a lot less area.  The standard 2D maps are quite deceptive.</p><p>OTOH, Siberia has a lot of land at each of the higher latitudes (until you reach the sea).  Unfortunately, that's land that has been under permafrost, and when it thaws it's not very useful for either crops or living space.  (Think of it as a rotting icy swamp.,,much of which is highly acidic and full of poisonous minerals, but not full enough to be worth refining.)</p></div>
	</div>

